subtitle: In this lecture, we will study the concept of hamiltonian Cycle, which is based on the backtracking approach. We will learn the concept of hamiltonian Cycle. For this,you have to remember two points. The first point is that in a hamiltonian Cycle, the starting and ending vertex should be the same, which means it should end at the same vertex from which it started. The second point is that you have to remember that all the vertices of the graph have to be visited exactly once. For visiting, a depth first search algorithm is used.Now, we have to see the definition of hamiltonian Cycle. So,youcan define it this way: A hamiltonian cycle is a path starting from any vertex and ending at that same vertex, visiting all the vertices exactly once here you have to remember one concept: traveling salesman problem is also similar to hamiltonian Cycle.In traveling salesman Problem, there is an optimal path whose cost is minimum, whereas in hamiltonian Cycle, more than one solution exists. Soin this we use back tracking approach

id: AR-15 Gas System [ml9tpzQ5BWs]
subtitle: AR-15 Gas system As the expanding gases propel the bullet down the barrel,a portion escapes through the gas port.This high pressure gas quickly travels through the gas tube leading to a chamber between the bolt and the carrier the dwell time is the time the bullet spends between the gas port and the muzzle.The pressure from the gas trapped behind the bullet is necessary to cycle the rifle.The chamber between the bolt and carrier acts as a pneumatic cylinder since the bolt can not move forward the pressure forces the carrier to the rear.As the bullet clears the muzzle, the pressure drops and at this point the carrier has picked up enough inertia to retract the bolt.The two vents on the carrier pass over the gas rings on the bolt releasing the gases from the chamber the bolt carrier continues to the rear as it extracts the empty shell case.

subtitle: As I told you earlier any object, even you,can turn into a black hole if squeezed to a certain extent. but how does an object actually become a black hole?Look, all matter has gravity, and gravity depends on the mass of the object and its distance. the farther away the matter is, the weaker its gravity for example, when you stand on a plant, your body feels the gravity of all the atoms of that plant,even the farthest atom of that planet because of this, you are standing properly on that plant. The same thing happens with the Earth and its gravity. But if you squeeze that plant and make it smaller, all the atoms will come very close to each other, due to which you will be able to feel the gravity of that planet evenmore. And if you keep squeezing that planet even more, then ata certain point, that planet will become so small that even light can not reflect from it. And thus that planet will convert into a black hole.
